# If you prefer a global ignore file, keep this minimal.

# Binaries
bin/
dist/**
dist/config.yaml
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

.DS_Store
node_modules
.turbo
*.log
dist
*.local
.env
.cache
server/dist
public/dist
**/.vitepress/dist/**
**/.vitepress/cache/**
.netlify
bin
.vscode

# Go build artifacts
*.test
*.out
*.cover
coverage.out
coverage.html

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
.trae

# cgo / compiler outputs
*.o
*.a
*.obj

# Logs
*.log

# SQLite databases (test artifacts)
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-shm
*.sqlite-wal

# Checked-in test fixtures are real test data, not runtime output. The
# generic artifact rules above (*.log, *.sqlite, ...) must never silently
# drop fixture files — e.g. archon evidence logs (exploit.log, attempts.log,
# confirm-test-output.log) under the harness fixture corpus. No parent dir of
# these is ignored, so this file-level negation re-includes them.
!test/testdata/archon-audit-data/**

# Test workspace artifacts (state exports from executor tests)
internal/executor/*/run-*.json
internal/executor/*/run-*.yaml
test/integration/*-test/
!test/integration/*_test.go

# Audit output dirs written by the harnesses into <source>/<harness-name>/
# whenever vigolium is self-audited (e.g. `vigolium agent archon --source .`).
# Excludes the harness embedded resources under internal/resources/archon/.
/archon/
/piolium/
**/archon/audit-state.json
**/archon/audit-context.md
**/archon/findings/
**/archon/findings-draft/
**/archon/longshot/
**/archon/attack-surface/
**/piolium/audit-state.json
**/piolium/file-records/
**/piolium/attack-surface/
**/piolium/findings-draft/

# some binaries and outputs from the skill that we don't want to accidentally commit
# better to ignore the whole directory since there are multiple outputs and it can be hard to keep track of them all
public/presets/deparos/jsscan/jsscan-*
internal/resources/deparos/jsscan/*

internal/resources/spitolas/chromium/*

# sometimes the skill just build a binary in the root of the repo, so let's ignore that too
./vigolium

.claude
OPTIMIZE.md
OPTIMIZE-*.md
PLANNING.md
PLANNING-*.md
INTERNAL.md
INTERNAL-*.md
vigolium
build/dist-license/
build/dist-public/
build/dist-npm/

# Private deployment infra — never publish to the open-source repo
platform/vigolium-console/
